name: Electrification plan
information: Draw up plans using computer-aided design and building information modelling software

name: Analyse  plans and drawings
information: Analyse architectural plans and drawings, highlighting any possible risks or problems and making amendments using computer-aided design applications (CAD)

name: Specify technology and tools
information: Specify the appropriate technology and tools to be used in the project and advising where this requires deviation from the initial design plans

name: Documents for approvals
information: Prepare documents to help with getting planning permission and similar approvals

name: Spec for road construction
information: Compiling job specs and supervising tendering procedures

name: Fields analysis
information: Planning, organising and undertaking field work/site investigations by creating boreholes and trial pits

name: Issuing approval for building work
information: Issuing approval to start building work and completion certificates

name: Impact on transportation
information: Assessing the impact of recent building developments, such as a new housing estate, on transport systems

name: Traffic modelling
information: Modelling traffic flows using mathematical techniques and specialist computer applications

name: Information resources
information: Producing educational or information resources for internal staff, clients or the general public
